- Explain the Three Tier architecture

* Three Tier architecture is an architectural deployment style that describe the separation of functionality into layers with each segment being a tier(Presentaion tier, Logic tier and Data tier). Each tier is developed and maintained as an independent tier.

Presentaion tier - The presentation layer provides the application's user interface.

Logic tier - The Logic tier controls an application's functionality by performing detailed processing.

Data tier - Data base, this is where information is stored and retrieved.


- Explain the MVC pattern

* MVC is a software architectural pattern for implementing user interfaces. Model, View, Controller.

Model - Buissness rules / Applications data

View - UI/presentation

Controller - Communication between users and the Model.
